subject: Password reset issue
answer:
Hello,

Here’s the information related to your request:

• To reset your password, go to the login page and click on the "Forgot Password" link. You will receive an email with a reset link. Follow the instructions in the email to set a new password.
• The reset link remains valid for 30 minutes from the time it is issued.
• Check your spam folder and ensure you are using the correct registered email address. If the issue persists, contact customer support.
• Yes. You can update your email address under Account Settings → Personal Information.

If this does not resolve your issue, the ticket will be escalated.

Regards,
Support Team

subject: Diabetes symptoms
answer:
Hello,

Based on our medical knowledge base, here is the relevant information:

- Diabetes is a chronic metabolic disease characterized by elevated blood glucose levels.
It occurs when the pancreas does not produce enough insulin or when the body cannot effectively use the insulin it produces.

Common symptoms of diabetes include frequent urination, excessive thirst, increased hunger, unexplained weight loss, fatigue, blurred vision, and slow healing of wounds.
Some individuals...

- Type 1 diabetes and Type 2 diabetes.
Type 1 diabetes is an autoimmune condition in which the immune system attacks insulin-producing cells.
Type 2 diabetes is associated with insulin resistance and is often linked to lifestyle factors such as obesity and physical inactivity.
